value.value: A procedure in which tissue desiccation is achieved via employment of a moderately damped alternating electrical current.
A Uralic language of the Finnic branch, spoken as the official language of Estonia.
A language isolate spoken in the Basque country of Spain and France. Basque is unrelated to the other languages of Europe or to any other known living language.
A Niger-Congo language spoken in southeastern Ghana, part of a cluster of related languages commonly called Gbe.
A Niger-Congo language spoken by the Ewondo people of Cameroon.
A Niger-Congo, Bantu language spoken in Cameroon, Gabon, Equatorial Guinea, Sao Tome and Principe, and the Congo Republic.
An Indo-European, North Germanic language spoken mainly on the Faroe Islands and parts of Denmark.
A Western Iranian language within the Indo-Iranian branch of the Indo-European language family primarily spoken in Iran, Afghanistan, and Tajikistan.
One of the three formal literary dialects of the Akan language. It is the major local dialect in the Central Region of Ghana, as well as in other regions from mid to southern Ghana.
An Austronesian language of the Malayo-Polynesian family spoken by ethnic Fijians as a native language.
A Finnic language spoken by a majority of the population in Finland and by ethnic Finns outside Finland.
The removal of excess fluid via needle puncture from the thoracic cavity.
A Niger-Congo language, part of the Eastern Gbe language cluster, spoken mainly in Benin.
A part of the larger group of the West Germanic Frisian languages, spoken in the North Frisia area of Germany.
A West Low German, Friso-Saxon dialect spoken in the East Frisian peninsula of northwestern Lower Saxony state of Germany.
A West Germanic language spoken mostly in the province of Friesland in the north of the Netherlands.
A Niger-Congo language spoken as a set of various dialects in a continuum that stretches across 20 countries in West and Central Africa.
An Indo-European Romance language spoken in the Friuli region of northeastern Italy.
A Niger-Congo Kwa language spoken in the capital area of Ghana.
An Austronesian language spoken in the mountainous region of Aceh, Central Aceh, Bener Meriah, and Gayo Lues regencies of Indonesia.
A family of languages spoken mainly in the Central African Republic, Cameroon, the Democratic Republic of the Congo, and the Republic of the Congo.
A Micronesian language of the Austronesian language family native to the island of Kiribati.
An Indo-European Celtic language native to the Gaels of Scotland.
An Indo-European Celtic language originating in Ireland and historically spoken by the Irish people.
An Indo-European language of the Western Ibero-Romance branch spoken in the Galicia community of northwestern Spain.
An Indo-European Celtic language spoken as a first language by the Manx people on the Isle of Man.
A South-Central Dravidian language, spoken chiefly in the Indian states of Madhya Pradesh, Gujarat, Telangana, Maharashtra, Chhattisgarh, and Andhra Pradesh.
An Austronesian language spoken in the Gorontalo Province of Indonesia by the Gorontaloan people.
A Niger-Congo Kru language spoken in Liberia.
A language in the Tup-Guarani branch of the Tupi linguistic family that is an indigenous language in Latin America.
Any of the Alemannic dialects spoken in the German-speaking part of Switzerland and in some Alpine communities in Northern Italy bordering Switzerland.
An Indo-Aryan language native to the Indian state of Gujarat.

An Athabaskan language spoken by the Gwich'in First Nation in Canada and the Alaska Native People of the United States.
A language isolate that is the language of the Haida people, spoken in the Haida Gwaii archipelago off the northern Pacific coast of Canada and on Prince of Wales Island in Alaska.
A French-based creole language native to Haiti.
An Afro-Asiatic Chadic language native to Niger, Nigeria, Ghana, Benin, Cameroon, Ivory Coast, Togo and Sudan.
A Polynesian language native to the Hawaiian islands of the United States.
A Northwest Semitic language native to Israel.
A Niger-Congo Bantu language spoken by the Herero and Mbanderu peoples in Namibia and Botswana.
An Austronesian regional language spoken in the Philippines.
A standardized and Sanskritized register of the Hindustani language.
A simplified version of Motu that is an official language of Papua New Guinea.

Bone marrow transfer in which the patient is his own donor.  Bone marrow is removed prior to bone marrow ablation treatment and then returned to reconstitute the hematopoietic system. Prior to reinfusion the bone marrow is often treated to purge it of residual tumor cells.
The standardized variety of the Serbo-Croatian language used by Croats, principally in Croatia, Bosnia and Herzegovina.
An Indo-European language spoken by Sorbs in the province of Upper Lusatia in Germany.
An Athabaskan language spoken along the lower course of the Trinity River in Northwestern California by the Hupa people.
An Indo-European language spoken as the official language of Armenia.
An Austronesian language spoken by the Iban people of the Malaysian state of Sarawak, the Indonesian province of West Kalimantan, and in Brunei.
